latestPosts.caption: Starting with UGC in June definitely changed things for me and I hope my December month can inspire someone to start posting more💁🏻‍♀️ In the beginning of 2024 I was now and then doing some collaborations for a small amount of money. I did not know that much about the rates and did not know that much about creating engaging content even though I’ve always loved to post and be active here. But this year I started to learn more about it and the more I learned and the more I posted I started to get inbounds. I would say June was the month I truly started to actively search for opportunities, tried to learn more about UGC and quite fast got so much better at it ( If I can say so myself)🫶🏻 The more brands I worked with, the more brands reached out to me. I also pitched to some brands. During the autumn it took off for me a bit more and let me tell you that my January 2025 is my best month so far🙈 Not so Swedish of me to post something like this. But who cares? Let’s get inspired, because I am. It is growing, I am growing and 2025 will be amazing 🫶🏻

Another week in this amazing place. The weather has been a bit rainy this week but we’ve still enjoyed our little village, Marino, where we stay at the moment. The first of November we move into our new apartment in Rome where we will stay for at least a year. I’m so excited 🙈
WE’RE PREGNANT🤰Today we move into week 13 and in October we will have one more little family member👶🍼 So happy to be doing this with @henrik.fallenius 🥹 Love you!!❤️
😎😎😎

latestPosts.caption: All I want to wear this summer is transparent skirts 💁🏼‍♀️

Today we’re leaving Corfu🌴 It’s been an amazing trip and the perfect blend of activities and relaxing. I would definately recommend Corfu to anyone 🫶🏻 Some of my favorites from the trip was Rovinia beach, La grotta beach bar, all the greek salads in my sunbed, the genuine tavernas, the people and service? Ambelonas wineyard, Corfu town and  Akron Beach club✨ Thank you Corfu!
